text: Maaninka is a former municipality in the middle of Northern Savonia, Finland. It had over 3,750 people living there in January 2014. The municipalities next to it are Iisalmi, Kuopio, Lapinlahti, Pielavesi, Siilinj√§rvi and Tervo. ==History== Maaninka was established in 1872.http://www.maaninka.fi/00010364-kunnan-historiaa finnish It was merged with the city of Kuopio on 1 January 2015. ==References== == Other websites == * The official Maaninka page Category:Former municipalities of Finland
